{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":897,"text":"Sarge Salman: All the way from\nLos Altos Hills, California,"},{"time":3293,"text":"Mr. Henry Evans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":5354,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":20477,"text":"Henry Evans: Hello."},{"time":22105,"text":"My name is Henry Evans,"},{"time":23960,"text":"and until August 29, 2002,"},{"time":27551,"text":"I was living my version of the American dream."},{"time":32575,"text":"I grew up in a typical American town near St. Louis."},{"time":37073,"text":"My dad was a lawyer."},{"time":38928,"text":"My mom was a homemaker."},{"time":41917,"text":"My six siblings and I were good kids,"},{"time":44368,"text":"but caused our fair share of trouble."},{"time":47860,"text":"After high school, I left home to study"},{"time":50250,"text":"and learn more about the world."},{"time":53153,"text":"I went to Notre Dame University"},{"time":55810,"text":"and graduated with degrees\nin accounting and German,"},{"time":59356,"text":"including spending a year of study in Austria."},{"time":62300,"text":"Later on, I earned an MBA at Stanford."},{"time":67181,"text":"I married my high school sweetheart, Jane."},{"time":71193,"text":"I am lucky to have her."},{"time":73555,"text":"Together, we raised four wonderful children."},{"time":78200,"text":"I worked and studied hard\nto move up the career ladder,"},{"time":81281,"text":"eventually becoming a chief financial officer"},{"time":83676,"text":"in Silicon Valley, a job I really enjoyed."},{"time":88476,"text":"My family and I bought our first and only home"},{"time":91253,"text":"on December 13, 2001,"},{"time":95089,"text":"a fixer-upper in a beautiful spot"},{"time":97298,"text":"of Los Altos Hills, California,"},{"time":99738,"text":"from where I am speaking to you now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":102974,"text":"We were looking forward to rebuilding it,"},{"time":105584,"text":"but eight months after we moved in,"},{"time":107819,"text":"I suffered a stroke-like attack\ncaused by a birth defect."},{"time":112211,"text":"Overnight, I became a mute quadriplegic"},{"time":117150,"text":"at the ripe old age of 40."},{"time":120493,"text":"It took me several years,"},{"time":122646,"text":"but with the help of an incredibly supportive family,"},{"time":126215,"text":"I finally decided life was still worth living."},{"time":131074,"text":"I became fascinated with using technology"},{"time":133619,"text":"to help the severely disabled."},{"time":138043,"text":"Head tracking devices sold commercially"},{"time":140565,"text":"by the company Madentec"},{"time":143316,"text":"convert my tiny head movements\ninto cursor movements,"},{"time":147174,"text":"and enable my use of a regular computer."},{"time":151460,"text":"I can surf the web, exchange email with people,"},{"time":154719,"text":"and routinely destroy my friend Steve Cousins"},{"time":157647,"text":"in online word games."},{"time":159764,"text":"This technology allows me to remain engaged,"},{"time":162650,"text":"mentally active,"},{"time":164003,"text":"and feel like I am a part of the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":167754,"text":"One day, I was lying in bed watching CNN,"},{"time":171059,"text":"when I was amazed by Professor Charlie Kemp"},{"time":173645,"text":"of the Healthcare Robotics Lab at Georgia Tech"},{"time":176396,"text":"demonstrating a PR2 robot."},{"time":179240,"text":"I emailed Charlie and\nSteve Cousins of Willow Garage,"},{"time":183287,"text":"and we formed the Robots for Humanity project."},{"time":188139,"text":"For about two years, Robots for Humanity"},{"time":191040,"text":"developed ways for me to use the PR2"},{"time":193421,"text":"as my body surrogate."},{"time":196801,"text":"I shaved myself for the first time in 10 years."},{"time":201894,"text":"From my home in California,"},{"time":203668,"text":"I shaved Charlie in Atlanta. (Laughter)"},{"time":207647,"text":"I handed out Halloween candy."},{"time":212064,"text":"I opened my refrigerator on my own."},{"time":218091,"text":"I began doing tasks around the house."},{"time":222163,"text":"I saw new and previously unthinkable possibilities"},{"time":225731,"text":"to live and contribute,"},{"time":228396,"text":"both for myself and others in my circumstance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":233022,"text":"All of us have disabilities in one form or another."},{"time":237630,"text":"For example, if either of us\nwants to go 60 miles an hour,"},{"time":243056,"text":"both of us will need an assistive device called a car."},{"time":248400,"text":"Your disability doesn't make you\nany less of a person,"},{"time":251716,"text":"and neither does mine."},{"time":254140,"text":"By the way, check out my sweet ride. (Laughter)"},{"time":258913,"text":"Since birth, we have both suffered from the inability"},{"time":261810,"text":"to fly on our own."}]},{"cues":[{"time":264754,"text":"Last year, Kaijen Hsiao of Willow Garage"},{"time":268864,"text":"connected with me Chad Jenkins."},{"time":271436,"text":"Chad showed me how easy it is"},{"time":273909,"text":"to purchase and fly aerial drones."},{"time":277565,"text":"It was then I realized that I could also use"},{"time":280153,"text":"an aerial drone to expand the worlds"},{"time":282381,"text":"of bedridden people through flight,"},{"time":285519,"text":"giving a sense of movement and control"},{"time":288442,"text":"that is incredible."},{"time":291519,"text":"Using a mouse cursor I control with my head,"},{"time":294396,"text":"these web interfaces allow me"},{"time":296285,"text":"to see video from the robot"},{"time":297895,"text":"and send control commands"},{"time":299528,"text":"by pressing buttons in a web browser."},{"time":303255,"text":"With a little practice, I became\ngood enough with this interface"},{"time":307164,"text":"to drive around my home on my own."},{"time":313884,"text":"I could look around our garden"},{"time":316592,"text":"and see the grapes we are growing."},{"time":320702,"text":"I inspected the solar panels on our roof. (Laughter)"},{"time":326722,"text":"One of my challenges as a pilot is to land the drone"},{"time":329721,"text":"on our basketball hoop."},{"time":335257,"text":"I went even further by seeing if I could use"},{"time":337688,"text":"a head-mounted display, the Oculus Rift,"},{"time":340711,"text":"as modified by Fighting Walrus,"},{"time":342759,"text":"to have an immersive experience"},{"time":344406,"text":"controlling the drone."},{"time":348361,"text":"With Chad's group at Brown,"},{"time":350288,"text":"I regularly fly drones around his lab"},{"time":352768,"text":"several times a week,\nfrom my home 3,000 miles away."},{"time":358517,"text":"All work and no fun makes for a dull quadriplegic,"},{"time":362042,"text":"so we also find time to play friendly games"},{"time":365072,"text":"of robot soccer. (Laughter)"},{"time":368789,"text":"I never thought I would be able to casually"},{"time":371179,"text":"move around a campus like Brown on my own."},{"time":376151,"text":"I just wish I could afford the tuition. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":384505,"text":"Chad Jenkins: Henry, all joking aside,"},{"time":386953,"text":"I bet all of these people here"},{"time":389142,"text":"would love to see you fly this drone"},{"time":391348,"text":"from your bed in California 3,000 miles away."}]},{"cues":[{"time":394513,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":405540,"text":"Okay, Henry, have you been to D.C. lately?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":409330,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":412838,"text":"Are you excited to be at TEDxMidAtlantic?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":416347,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":423901,"text":"Can you show us how excited you are?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":426831,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":431113,"text":"All right, big finish."},{"time":432764,"text":"Can you show us how good of a pilot you are?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":437818,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":442468,"text":"All right, we still have a little ways to go with that,"},{"time":444954,"text":"but I think it shows the promise."}]},{"cues":[{"time":447466,"text":"What makes Henry's story amazing"},{"time":450102,"text":"is it's about understanding Henry's needs,"},{"time":453230,"text":"understanding what people in Henry's situation"},{"time":456224,"text":"need from technology,"},{"time":458133,"text":"and then also understanding"},{"time":459790,"text":"what advanced technology can provide,"},{"time":462168,"text":"and then bringing those two things together"},{"time":464241,"text":"for use in a wise and responsible way."},{"time":467483,"text":"What we're trying to do is democratize robotics,"},{"time":469593,"text":"so that anybody can be a part of this."},{"time":471494,"text":"We're providing affordable,\noff-the-shelf robot platforms"},{"time":474490,"text":"such as the A.R. drone, 300 dollars,"},{"time":477030,"text":"the Suitable Technologies beam,\nonly 17,000 dollars,"},{"time":481618,"text":"along with open-source robotics software"},{"time":483978,"text":"so that you can be a part of what we're trying to do."},{"time":486155,"text":"And our hope is that, by providing these tools,"},{"time":489039,"text":"that you'll be able to think of better ways"},{"time":490687,"text":"to provide movement for the disabled,"},{"time":492588,"text":"to provide care for our aging population,"},{"time":495310,"text":"to help better educate our children,"},{"time":497294,"text":"to think about what the new types"},{"time":499608,"text":"of middle class jobs could be for the future,"},{"time":502200,"text":"to both monitor and protect our environment,"},{"time":504803,"text":"and to explore the universe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":506882,"text":"Back to you, Henry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":510813,"text":"HE: Thank you, Chad."}]},{"cues":[{"time":513599,"text":"With this drone setup, we show the potential"},{"time":516421,"text":"for bedridden people to once again be able"},{"time":518887,"text":"to explore the outside world,"},{"time":521558,"text":"and robotics will eventually provide"},{"time":523935,"text":"a level playing field"},{"time":525278,"text":"where one is only limited by their mental acuity"},{"time":527981,"text":"and imagination,"},{"time":530226,"text":"where the disabled are able to perform"},{"time":532385,"text":"the same activities as everyone else,"},{"time":535080,"text":"and perhaps better,"},{"time":537982,"text":"and technology will even allow us to provide"},{"time":540622,"text":"an outlet for many people who are presently"},{"time":542783,"text":"considered vegetables."},{"time":545211,"text":"One hundred years ago,"},{"time":547218,"text":"I would have been treated like a vegetable."},{"time":550569,"text":"Actually, that's not true."},{"time":552999,"text":"I would have died."}]},{"cues":[{"time":555194,"text":"It is up to us, all of us, to decide how"},{"time":558016,"text":"robotics will be used, for good or for evil,"},{"time":561381,"text":"for simply replacing people"},{"time":563006,"text":"or for making people better,"},{"time":564643,"text":"for allowing us to do and enjoy more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":568583,"text":"Our goal for robotics is to\nunlock everyone's mental power"},{"time":572209,"text":"by making the world more physically accessible"},{"time":574878,"text":"to people such as myself and others like me"},{"time":577421,"text":"around the globe."},{"time":579603,"text":"With the help of people like you,"},{"time":581486,"text":"we can make this dream a reality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":584626,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":587307,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}